<item>
            <title>[LDAP-335] NoClassDefFoundError: RepositoryConfigurationExtension</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/LDAP-335</link>
                <project id="10071" key="LDAP">Spring LDAP</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This seems to have been caused by changes for issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/LDAP-311&quot; title=&quot;Fix optional dependencies in spring-ldap-core&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LDAP-311&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LDAP-311&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When starting up an application that uses Spring LDAP with XML config, the exception is thrown on init:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.springframework.beans.FatalBeanException: Invalid NamespaceHandler class &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;org.springframework.ldap.config.LdapNamespaceHandler&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; for namespace &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/schema/ldap&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/schema/ldap&lt;/a&gt;: problem with handler class file or dependent class; nested exception is java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: org/springframework/data/repository/config/RepositoryConfigurationExtension&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding spring-data-commons dependency resolves this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows 7, Java 7 JDK, JBoss EAP 6.4, Tomcat 7.0.59</environment>
